From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Tue, 10 Feb 2026 21:18:47 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] xhci: plat: auto-detect USB3 LPM support for ACPI platform
 controllers

Under DT, USB3 LPM (Link Power Management) is enabled by the
usb3-lpm-capable property.  ACPI platform controllers lack this
property, but the hardware capability is reported in HCSPARAMS3.

Auto-enable XHCI_LPM_SUPPORT when running on an ACPI platform
controller that reports non-zero U1/U2 exit latencies, so USB3
devices can enter low-power link states without needing DT
properties.
---
 drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c | 13 +++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c b/drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c
index 0baa3be7618c8..c6be3321cac75 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c
@@ -90,6 +90,19 @@ static void xhci_plat_quirks(struct device *dev, struct xhci_hcd *xhci)
 	struct xhci_plat_priv *priv = xhci_to_priv(xhci);
 
 	xhci->quirks |= priv->quirks;
+
+	/*
+	 * For ACPI platform controllers, auto-detect LPM support from
+	 * hardware capability registers.  Under DT, the usb3-lpm-capable
+	 * property is used instead (set from device properties in probe).
+	 * If HCS_PARAMS3 reports non-zero U1/U2 exit latencies, the
+	 * controller supports USB3 LPM.
+	 */
+	if (!(xhci->quirks & XHCI_LPM_SUPPORT) &&
+	    is_acpi_device_node(dev_fwnode(dev)) &&
+	    (HCS_U1_LATENCY(xhci->hcs_params3) |
+	     HCS_U2_LATENCY(xhci->hcs_params3)))
+		xhci->quirks |= XHCI_LPM_SUPPORT;
 }
 
 /* called during probe() after chip reset completes */
